==English==
===Etymology===
From the Old French ''[[esplen]]'', from Latin ''[[splen|spl&#275;n]]'', from Greek.

===Pronunciation===
*splēn, /spliːn/, /<tt>spli:n</tt>/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-iːn|Rhymes: -iːn]]

===Noun===
'''spleen''' ([[spleens]])

#An [[organ]] of the body that consists of [[lymphatic]] tissues and stores up nutrient-filled oxygenated [[blood]] to provide a burst of energy in emergencies.
#(''archaic, except in the [[set phrase]] ''"to [[vent#Transitive verb|vent]] one's spleen") A bad [[mood]]; [[spite]]fulness.

